Select Data

State_Enrollments<-filter(Enrollments,District=="State")
State_Enrollments

Line Chart for State Enrollments by Year by School

State_Enrollments$School<-factor(State_Enrollments$School,
levels=c("Elementary","High School","Middle","Kindergarten"))
ggplot(State_Enrollments,aes(x=Year,y=Enrollment,color=School))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_line(size=1)+
  geom_text(aes(label=Enrollment),vjust=-0.5,size=3)+
  labs(title="NH Fall Enrollments by School 2019-2024\nZin Min Thant")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))

library(ggplot2)
Manchester_Enrollments<-filter(Enrollments,District=="Manchester")
str(Manchester_Enrollments)
## 'data.frame':    24 obs. of  5 variables:
##  $ Number    : int  1 8 15 22 29 36 43 50 57 64 ...

##  $ School    : chr  "Kindergarten" "Elementary" "Middle" "High School" ...
##  $ Enrollment: int  860 3637 3503 3448 839 4167 2993 3472 867 4144 ...
Manchester_Enrollments$School<-factor(Manchester_Enrollments$School,
levels=c("Elementary","High School","Middle","Kindergarten"))
ggplot(Manchester_Enrollments,aes(x=Year,y=Enrollment,color=School))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_line(show.legend ="FALSE" )+
  geom_text(aes(label=Enrollment),vjust=-0.5,size=3)+
  labs(title="Manchester Fall Enrollments by School 2019-2024\nZin Min Thant")+theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust=0.5))
